'''''2002 FIFA World Cup''''', sometimes known as '''''FIFA World Cup 2002''''', is the second [[EA Sports]] official [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] video game developed by [[EA Canada]] and [[Software Creations (UK)|Creations]], with [[Intelligent Games]] assisting for PS2, Xbox, Windows, and Nintendo GameCube platform and [[Tose (company)|Tose Software]] also assisting the GameCube version, the game was published by EA Sports in North America and Europe and published by [[Electronic Arts Victor]] in Japan.

An amalgamation between the game engines of ''[[FIFA Football 2002]]'' and ''[[FIFA Football 2003]]'', the game still incorporates the power bar for shots and crosses but with a steeper [[learning curve]] and customisation of the chances of being penalised by the match [[Referee (association football)|referee]]. Some kits are licensed, along with player likeness and the stadia of the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]]. Unlike the previous games in the FIFA series, the game had an original soundtrack performed by the [[Vancouver Symphony Orchestra]].
It was released for [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]], [[PlayStation 2]], [[Nintendo GameCube]], and [[Xbox (console)|Xbox]].

==Teams==
The game features each of the [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification#Qualified teams|32 teams that qualified]] for the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]], and 9 teams that did not qualify.

