{{Notability|Products|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox video game |title=Dungeonland |image= |developer=[[Critical Studio]] |publisher=[[Paradox Interactive]] |designer=[[Mark Venturelli]], [[Gabriel Ribeiro Teixeira]] |engine=[[Unity (game engine)|Unity]] |released='''Microsoft Windows'''{{vgrelease|[[International|INT]]|January 29, 2013}}'''Mac OS X'''{{vgrelease|[[International|INT]]|May 21, 2013}} |genre=[[Action role-playing game|Action role-playing]] |modes=[[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer]] |platforms=[[Microsoft Windows]], [[Mac OS X]] }}
'''''Dungeonland''''' is a [[Cooperative gameplay|cooperative]] [[action role-playing game]], made by Brazilian developer [[Critical Studio]], using the [[Unity (game engine)|Unity]] engine. The game was released on January 29, 2013 for Windows, with a Mac OS X release scheduled for a later date.<ref name=source />
==Gameplay== ''Dungeonland'' is a [[multiplayer]] [[hack & slash]]/[[dungeon crawler game]], which takes place in a [[theme park]] controlled by a 'Dungeon Maestro'. The game features an [[Isometric graphics in video games and pixel art|isometric camera]], and a series of maps with no storyline present. The game features simultaneous local and online multiplayer.
It is also possible for a fourth player to play as the Dungeon Maestro against the other players. They gain cards that can be spent with mana points to create obstacles such as killer rabbits, exploding frogs, or giant fans.
==Development== In November 2013, a [[free-to-play]] version of the game was released through [[Valve Corporation|Valve]]'s [[Steam (software)|Steam]] platform.<ref name="Puleo">{{cite web|url=http://www.co-optimus.com/article/11122/dungeonland-gets-free-to-play-version.html|title=DungeonLand Gets Free to Play Version|last=Puleo|first=Nick|date=20 November 2013|work=[[Co-Optimus]]|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref> The game's publisher [[Paradox Interactive]] initially had planned to develop ''Dungeonland'' into a [[media franchise|franchise]].<ref name="Reynolds">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/gaming/news/a455411/dungeonland-to-become-ongoing-franchise-reveals-paradox-interactive.html|title='Dungeonland' to become ongoing franchise, reveals Paradox Interactive|last=Reynolds|first=Matthew|date=31 January 2013|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref>
Dungeonland was shut down by Paradox on April 18th, 2018.<ref name="Shutdown">{{cite web|url=https://steamcommunity.com/app/218130/discussions/0/1697168437859518968/|title='Dungeonland Servers Closing}}</ref>
