{{Orphan|date=November 2018}}
'''Lomelda''' is the stage name of musician '''Hannah Read'''. According to Reed, Lomelda is a made up word that means "echo of the stars".<ref name="timeout">{{cite web|last1=Pelly|first1=Liz|title=Lomelda navigates growing up and leaving home on her debut album, Thx|url=https://www.timeout.com/newyork/news/lomelda-navigates-growing-up-and-leaving-home-on-her-debut-album-thx-011618|publisher=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref>
==Career== Hannah Read was raised in [[Silsbee, Texas]].<ref name="stereogum">{{cite web|last1=Rettig|first1=James|title=Lomelda Bring Starry-Eyed Texas Romanticism To SXSW|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1930163/lomelda-bring-starry-eyed-texas-romanticism-to-sxsw/concert/|publisher=[[Stereogum]]|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref> She began her music career playing in bands with her brother as well as her high school friends.<ref name="thefader">{{cite web|last1=Mandel|first1=Leah|title=Lomelda Debuts "From Here," A Delicate Rock Ballad About Collapsing Distance|url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/08/16/lomelda-from-here-thx-stream-interview|publisher=[[The Fader]]|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref> Read's first full-length album, ''Forever'', was released in 2015.<ref name="goldflakepaint">{{cite web|last1=Johnson|first1=Tom|title=Lomelda: Forever|url=https://www.goldflakepaint.co.uk/feature-the-driving-romance-of-wacos-lomelda/|publisher=Gold Flake Paint|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref> In 2017, Read released her second full-length album, ''Thx'', with the independent record label [[Double Double Whammy]]. The album was co-produced with the assistance of Read's brother, Tommy.<ref name="vulture">{{cite web|last1=Geffen|first1=Sasha|title=Introducing Lomelda’s Sad Open-Road Music|url=http://www.vulture.com/2017/09/introducing-lomeldas-sad-songs-of-the-open-road.html|publisher=[[Vulture (magazine)|Vulture]]|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref> It was primarily written over a few months while Read was sleeping in her car.<ref name="stereogum1">{{cite web|last1=Rettig|first1=James|title=Band To Watch: Lomelda|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1950952/band-to-watch-lomelda/franchises/interview/|publisher=Stereogum|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref><ref name="uproxx">{{cite web|last1=Stoneback|first1=Stephanie|title=Small Town Texas’ Lomelda’s New Album ‘Thx’ Seeks Beauty In The Space Between You And Me|url=https://uproxx.com/music/lomelda-thx-interview-pinegrove-touring-double-double-whammy/|publisher=[[Uproxx]]|accessdate=24 April 2018}}</ref> In July 2017, Stereogum named Lomelda one of their "Bands To Watch".<ref name="stereogum1"/>
==Discography== '''Studio albums''' *Forever (2015) *Thx (2017, Double Double Whammy)
